cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OrderBench, please cite the accompanying paper."
title: "OrderBench: Measuring Cleanup-on-Exception in LLM-Generated Code"
abstract: >-
  A contamination-free, copyright-clean benchmark built on self-authored,
  instrumented mock APIs. It exposes a failure mode invisible to output-only
  benchmarks: code that returns correct results yet leaks resources, skips
  rollbacks, or unbalances locks on injected error paths.
authors:
  - family-names: "Authors"
    given-names: "OrderBench"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-30"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - large language models
  - code generation
  - resource management
  - evaluation
